    "description": "Nakamura Choukou Co., Ltd. develops, manufactures, and sells precision equipment, chemical fiber spinning nozzles, and therapeutic science-related products in Japan. The company operates through Special Precision Equipment Business; Chemical Fiber Spinning Nozzle Business; D-Next Business; and Materials Science Business segments. It offers DINA-PRISM, a diamond wire cutting tool for the slicing process of electronic materials used in solar batteries, LEDs, etc.; PHX-01, a diamond wire manufacturing equipment; and high-precision equipment comprising wear-resistant parts for use in the manufacturing of bearings, electronics, and machine tools, adsorption nozzles that are used to pick and place electronic parts, automatic nozzle cleaners for electronic part adsorbing nozzles, and micro reactor items, including automated flow reactors, micromixers, and mass flow controllers for gaseous reagents, as well as automatic nozzle cleaner. The company also designs, manufactures, and sells spinnerets, precision parts, and machinery units for synthetic and chemical fibers, and meltblown and spunlace nonwoven fabrics; manufactures and sells industrial equipment, such as shower plates, fuel injectors, and medical devices, as well as filters; and sells spinneret cleaning equipment and detergents. In addition, it is involved in the design and distribution of diamond-wire production machine and diamond-wire for semiconductor; design, manufacture, and distribution of chemical fiber spinning nozzle and its peripheral parts, nonwove-fabric production machine, and nonwoven-fabric peripheral nozzles; design, manufacture, and distribution of high-precision parts and tools; and development, manufacture, and distribution of nano-size zeolites. Nakamura Choukou Co., Ltd. was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Sakai, Japan."
